Finally, I can make a tiny contribution to the list.  The pacific plate is 
currently in the process of sliding under the continental plate that we're
sitting on.  this causes the sierras and the chocolate mountains, and i'm
not sure what else.  I dunno bout south america, or the rockies.

Something your simulation should tke into account is the relative thickness of
the different plates, and how that affects their momenta, and therefore how
their velocities change.  For example, were the india chunk younger (and 
lighter) it would not have been able to plow into asia with such striking
results.

